    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-09-28T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-09-28T13:00:00-05:00" n="620"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d620">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/2834</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Moscow</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PDC1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Poole</hi>
                    </persName>), <hi rend="italic">temporarily at Christiania, to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Christiania</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-09-28T19:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 28, 1918, 7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received September 29, 5.33 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I have come here with a view to accelerating if possible through the Norwegian
                    Government departure from Russia of the Americans <pb facs="0748" n="674"
                        xml:id="pg_674"/> mentioned my No. 9 of the 25th. Will return Stockholm
                    October 1. Norwegian Chargé d’Affaires, Petrograd, also here, having left
                    Petrograd 25th. He reports that special messenger has been sent to Tsaritsyn to
                    bring Vice Consuls <persName>Burri</persName> and <persName>Leonard</persName>
                    to Moscow and that <persName corresp="#p_CGV1">Chicherin</persName> has given
                    written order for their departure from Russia. <persName corresp="#p_CGV1"
                        >Chicherin</persName> also promises that <persName>Paul Anderson</persName>
                    will be released and permitted to depart. I am telegraphing <persName
                        corresp="#p_WMA1">Wardwell</persName> of the Red Cross to hasten in every
                    way his and <persName>Andrews</persName>’s leaving.</p>
                <p>Norwegian Chargé d’Affaires reports conditions unchanged at Petrograd on the day
                    of the departure, wholesale arrests continuing.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PDC1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Poole</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
